09/05/2004
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- The federal foreign ministry issued a statement Saturday (8 May) saying US Secretary of State Colin Powell is generally receptive to the Belgrade plan for Kosovo. Serbian-Montenegrin Foreign Minister Vuk Draskovic met with Powell in Washington late last week about the situation in Kosovo and Belgrade's co-operation on war crimes. During the talks, Draskovic stressed that the plan is just a starting point for resolving problems in the province.(B92, Tanjug - 08/05/04)
